args: Must you spend all of your time gadding\nabout? You should live with austerity\nin line with the goddess's teachings!
Hey, I know! Once Dragonyule finally\ncomes around...
What is the meaning of this?\nWhy have I been summoned here?
No one ＂summoned＂ you—it's a party!\nWe all wanted to thank you for everything\nyou've done for us.
You have saved us all on more than one\noccasion with your healing magic.
We just wanted a chance to show you\nhow grateful we are.
I appreciate the sentiment—but as one\nwho practices moderation in all things,\nI cannot possibly accept.
Be that as it may, I still cannot help\nbut want to see you happy.
Even your king has come to this festival—\nso enjoy it before I have you clapped in\nirons and taken away!
I do not mean to reject your kindness,\nyet I must follow the teachings of the\ngoddess above all else.
But Dragonyule is the goddess's birthday!\nSurely she wants everyone to have fun on\nher special day, right?
That is...a fair point. Very well.\nI shall join you—but only briefly!
That's more like it! Now c'mon—\nthe guest of honor sits over here.
Would you like something to drink?
Oh, the bottom of your glass is wet.\nLet me wipe it with my handkerchief.
Ha HA! Behold, your king brings the finest\nfood in all the land!
Hmm. You know, that Saint Starfall outfit\nrather suits you.
Let me liven things up with a song!\n♪♪♪
What a fine voice you have.
(So far, so good. If she can manage to\nhave fun today, that should soften her\nup a bit!)
If I may say, Hildegarde, you seem\nquieter than usual today.
Hmm. Well, it IS my first time at a party,\nso I do feel somewhat uncomfortable.\nPerhaps that is the reason.
Then allow me to teach you how to best\nenjoy such an occasion. Escorting fine\nladies is my role in life, after all.

Preposterous! If anyone is to instruct her
in such matters, it should be the most
important person here—and that is
clearly me!
As such, I will take the responsibility\nof entertaining our guest.
Bah! I know how to take care of flowers\nbetter than anyone. An amateur like you\nshould keep quiet and let me speak.
I have never known anyone NOT to\nappreciate the escort of royalty.\nNow begone, churl!
I fear I must decline both invitations.
Oh, for heaven's sake. Why must you both\nalways be like this?
(Uh oh—here comes the lecture.\nI've gotta stop this!)
So, Hildegarde! Here's something I bet you\ndidn't know—I can do magic tricks!
Now watch as I steal something of yours\nwithout taking a single step!
Ah, but there you would be wrong.\nFor in those seconds, I stole your gaze!
I think I shall be going now.\nWhere should I put my dishes?
(Damn it! Nothing's gonna change if\nshe's allowed to leave now!)
You're always trying to help us by putting\neveryone else before yourself...
But you can only keep doing that for so\nlong before you become exhausted!
Hmm. Do you truly believe such?
I do, yeah. And I also REALLY want you to\nstay here and have more fun!
Yeah, the kid's right! Isn't he, everyone?!
Bowstrings are the same as people—\nthey need to be loosened once in a while\nor they'll snap from the pressure.
The finest work comes from those who\nalso enjoy recreation.
You deserve a reward for all the hard work\nyou do. The goddess would never want you\nto deny yourself that.
So stay and have some more fun, okay?\nYou can always start breaking rocks\nor whatever tomorrow.
See, you know we're making sense.\nNow come on in, boys! Let's up the fun!
DID SOMEONE SAY ＂DANCE＂?!\n...Er, no? No one actually said that?\n...Well, I'm gonna dance ANYWAY!
With me, everyone! Right turn! Left turn!
Saint Starfall has a special gift for you:\na dancing lesson!
I will teach you the art of dancing if you\nbut take my hand.
There's no joy in simply sitting around on\noccasions like these. You need to have\nfun and unwind with the rest of us.
Oh, very well. In that case, I shall be\ncounting on the two of you.
Now THIS is what I call a celebration!
By the time it came to an end, everyone was\nconvinced their plan to make Hildegarde lighten\nup had been a rousing success. However...
Stop slacking! Dragonyule is over!\nWe must welcome in the new year\nwith solemnity and introspection!
What?! You're even stricter than ever!
We enjoyed ourselves during Dragonyule,\nwhich means we must live with even\nMORE austerity to restore the balance!
That goes for every facet of your life,\nso I expect you to look sharp!
This wasn't how it was supposed to gooo!
